            , were in a hay-loft together, consulting what they should do for victuals; and he said, that he and Peartree and James went out together, and that they broke my father-in-law's shop open, and took twenty one hats out; and that they carried the hats to that 
               <persName id="t17450911-30-person322">
                  Joseph 
                  James 
               <interp inst="t17450911-30-person322" type="surname" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450911-30-person322" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450911-30-person322" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and that he put a ladder out at the hay loft window, for them to come in to him, and they hid them till it was time for them to carry them to pawn; then a Constable was charged with them, till they went in search of Peartree .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17450911-30-person323">
                  William 
                  Rugley 
               <interp inst="t17450911-30-person323" type="surname" value="Rugley"></interp>
